doc.previous: The 25 January Revolution and the fall of Hosni Mubarak the following month ushered in a new artistic era reflecting a changed social and political environment;[389] "the revolution triggered a new public culture".[390] Since its beginning, artists played a significant role in the protests; street art and music (electro or techno sha'bi) were used to craft a public culture.[391] Artists documented and captured the essence of the revolution, distributing their art through online and face-to-face social networks.[392]
